# üìê UML Class Diagram ‚Äî Stock Notification (Observer Pattern)

### (Text-based UML ‚Äî exactly what interviewers expect on a whiteboard)

```
                 <<interface>>
        +------------------------------+
        |  StockNotificationObservable |
        +------------------------------+
        | +add(observer)               |
        | +remove(observer)            |
        | +notifySubscribers()         |
        | +setStockCount(int)          |
        | +getStockCount(): int        |
        +------------------------------+
                    ‚ñ≤
                    |
         implements  |
                    |
     +-----------------------------------+
     | IphoneStockObservableImpl         |
     +-----------------------------------+
     | - stockCount : int                |
     | - observers : List<NotificationObserver> |
     +-----------------------------------+
     | +add(observer)                    |
     | +remove(observer)                 |
     | +notifySubscribers()              |
     | +setStockCount(int)               |
     | +getStockCount(): int             |
     +-----------------------------------+
                    |
                    | maintains
                    | 1..*
                    ‚ñº
        +------------------------------+
        |  <<interface>>               |
        |  NotificationObserver        |
        +------------------------------+
        | +update()                    |
        +------------------------------+
                    ‚ñ≤
                    |
        --------------------------------
        |                              |
+-----------------------------+   +------------------------------+
| EmailNotificationObserver   |   | MobileNotificationObserver   |
+-----------------------------+   +------------------------------+
| - emailId : String          |   | - phoneNumber : String       |
| - observable : StockObservable | | - observable : StockObservable |
+-----------------------------+   +------------------------------+
| +update()                   |   | +update()                    |
+-----------------------------+   +------------------------------+
```

---

# üß† How to EXPLAIN this UML in an Interview (VERY IMPORTANT)

Say this **slowly and confidently**:

> ‚Äú`StockNotificationObservable` is the Subject interface.
> `IphoneStockObservableImpl` is the concrete subject that maintains stock state and a list of observers.
> `NotificationObserver` is the Observer interface with a single `update()` method.
> `EmailNotificationObserver` and `MobileNotificationObserver` are concrete observers that implement notification logic.
> When stock changes from zero to available, the observable notifies all registered observers by calling `update()`.‚Äù

That explanation alone is **10/10**.

---

# üîç Key Relationships (interviewer might ask)

### 1Ô∏è‚É£ Association (Observable ‚Üí Observer)

- One observable
- Many observers
- Stored as a `List`

üëâ _This is the core of Observer Pattern._

---

### 2Ô∏è‚É£ Interface-based dependency

- Observable depends on `NotificationObserver` (interface)
- Observers depend on `StockNotificationObservable` (interface)

üëâ _Loose coupling + DIP satisfied._

---

### 3Ô∏è‚É£ Runtime flow (quick version)

1. Client registers observers
2. Stock changes
3. Observable calls `notifySubscribers()`
4. Each observer‚Äôs `update()` executes

---

# üéØ If interviewer asks: ‚ÄúWhy not inheritance?‚Äù

Best answer:

> ‚ÄúBecause notification behavior varies independently of stock behavior. Composition via Observer Pattern avoids inheritance explosion and follows Open‚ÄìClosed Principle.‚Äù

---

# üß™ One-line summary (memorize this)

> ‚ÄúObserver Pattern establishes a one-to-many dependency where observers are notified automatically when the subject‚Äôs state changes, without tight coupling.‚Äù
